CLSI breakpoints for pip/tazo and cefepime applied to Pseudomonas spp.

Enterobacter, Citrobacter freundii, and Serratia may develop resistance during prolonged therapy with 3rd-generation cephalosporins as a result of derepression of AmpC B-lactamase. Therefore, isolates that are initially susceptible may become resistant within 3 to 4 days after start of therapy.
Levofloxacin susceptibilty not published, however Ciprofloxacin traditionally closely predicts levofloxacin activity for Pseudomonas
R = Intrinsic (i.e. not acquired) resistance. All wild-type isolates are expected to display resistance
